										<div class="toggle-content">
											<p>Hepatitis B is a serious disease that affects the liver.  It is caused by the hepatitis B virus.  Hepatitis B can cause mild illness lasting a few weeks, or it can lead to a serious, lifelong illness.
Hepatitis B virus infection can be either acute or chronic.
											</p>

											<ol class="list list-ordened list-ordened-style-2 mb-xlg mt-lg">
												<li>Hepatitis B is a serious liver disease caused by a virus.</li>
												<li> the virus remains in their body for years. During this time, the virus can attack the liver and cause serious problems like liver failure or cancer.</li>
												<li>Vaccination is the best way to prevent hepatitis B.</li>
											</ol>
										</div>
									</section>
